JOHANNESBURG - Afrotone Media Holdings says it has settled a vendor financing deal with Gupta-owned Oakbay.
	
	Afrotone says Oakbay will relinquish its hold on 24-hour news channel ANN7 and newspaper, The New Age. The two media companies were sold to former government spokesperson Mzwanele Manyi for R450-million through vendor financing. READ: Staff at Gupta-linked ANN7, New Age anxious over pay delays But it appears the parties have reached a new settlement deal. Afrotone chairperson Manyi says he hopes ANN7 can now reposition itself in the market. Earlier this year, MultiChoice announced it would not renew the channel's contract when it expires in August. eNCA